public interface CredentialValidationStrategy {  // Defining an Interface which will contain Strategy methods for credential validation. In real world applications, it's better to use strategy design pattern if there is any chance in your application to switch between different types of validations at runtime (like username-password/social security number).
    boolean validate(String userNameOrEmailAddress , String password); // Abstract method for implementing actual validation logic. 
}                                                               // Strategy Design Pattern: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strategy_pattern   / It's a behavioral design pattern, not strictly speaking about Java itself as it is more suited towards object-oriented programming principles like encapsulation and polymorphism (not the strict case for this example).